This paper discusses a generalized mean field theory for approximate inference in complex exponential family models. The paper is focused on machine learning and statistical inference, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses algorithms for approximate inference, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses optimization and convergence, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses information theory and dependency structures, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses control systems and convergence to locally optimal solutions, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
